    <p>Proof that sample variance from population without normality assumption also coverges to chi-squared distribution as n goes large<br /></p>

    <p>    $\large \frac{DF}{\sigma^{2}}\,S_{n}\, = \, \chi^{2}_{DF}$   (here, $\large DF$ equals to $\large \frac{2n}{\kappa\, -\, 1}$ and $\large \kappa$ is kurtosis) <br /></p>

